fields.Title: GARYS APARTMENT / DOOR
fields.Description: You can open this door when you get the key from Manana.

fields.Title: Door, Basement Apartment: "Someone is moving around in the apa..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Someone is moving around in the apartment. You hear the water being turned off and the sound of dishes clinking together.

fields.Title: Logic: "There *might* be important informat..."
fields.Dialogue Text: There *might* be important information in the apartment... I mean... there *might*...

fields.Title: Physical Instrument: "Good job. Let's go now. I'm sure th..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Good job. Let's go now. I'm sure there's *nothing* interesting in there.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""It is," the lieutenant remarks. "H..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It is," the lieutenant remarks. "However, we should definitely get the key from this 'Mañana' Evrart mentioned. That would drastically increase our credibility."

fields.Title: You: "Press your ear against the door."
fields.Dialogue Text: Press your ear against the door.

fields.Title: You: "Use Mañana's key to unlock the door..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Use Mañana's key to unlock the door.

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "Only *curiosity* could account for..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Only *curiosity* could account for stepping over that threshold. Maybe there's treasure in there? A white alligator? A fountain of quicksilver?

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: "The lieutenant merely nods in respo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The lieutenant merely nods in response.

fields.Title: Door, Basement Apartment: "The door has braved the elements fo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The door has braved the elements for decades. The copper nails holding the upholstery in place have turned green from sea air and so is the knocker, shaped like a lion's head.

fields.Title: Door, Basement Apartment: "The key stops mid-way in the lock...."
fields.Dialogue Text: The key stops mid-way in the lock. Something's blocking its path. You hear a dish smashing and shattering inside the apartment, then everything falls very silent.

fields.Title: Perception (Hearing): "You hear someone inside, walking fr..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You hear someone inside, walking from room to room... whoever lives here must be back home.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""That's probably the door Evrart me..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "That's probably the door Evrart mentioned. We still need to get the key from this Mañana first though."

fields.Title: Interfacing: "There's *nothing* else to do than l..."
fields.Dialogue Text: There's *nothing* else to do than leave and tell Evrart. No *conceivable* reason for you to intrude on the premises.

fields.Title: You: "Carefully knock."
fields.Dialogue Text: Carefully knock.

fields.Title: Door, Basement Apartment: "This must be the door Evrart mentio..."
fields.Dialogue Text: This must be the door Evrart mentioned. You still need to get the key from Mañana first though.

fields.Title: Shivers: "As you hold the opened door you can..."
fields.Dialogue Text: As you hold the opened door you can feel the air moving. A little draft. A whistle...

fields.Title: Perception (Hearing): "In fact, it's oddly silent in the y..."
fields.Dialogue Text: In fact, it's oddly silent in the yard around you. No birds chirp.

fields.Title: Interfacing: "The door is right here. You can jus..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The door is right here. You can just open it and be done with this.

fields.Title: Door, Basement Apartment: "The door to the 'Weasel's' Den', gu..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The door to the 'Weasel's' Den', guarded by the lionhead-knocker. Both have seen better days.

fields.Title: You: "Use Mañana's key to unlock the door..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Use Mañana's key to unlock the door.

fields.Title: Door, Basement Apartment: "The door to cryptofascist's shabby..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The door to cryptofascist's shabby apartment. It has been locked again.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Let's be honest, this isn't what I..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Let's be honest, this isn't what I joined the RCM for. But -- every day tells you something new about yourself..." the lieutenant replies, still inspecting the padded door.

fields.Title: Perception (Hearing): "A plate, glass or a mug."
fields.Dialogue Text: A plate, glass or a mug.

fields.Title: Interfacing: "The tenant's key is in the lock."
fields.Dialogue Text: The tenant's key is in the lock.

fields.Title: Door, Basement Apartment: "No answer."
fields.Dialogue Text: No answer.

fields.Title: Door, Basement Apartment: "Finally, the door unlocks with a sm..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Finally, the door unlocks with a small clack. Thoughts race through your head...

fields.Title: Endurance: "The Royal Lion. Guillaume's Kitten...."
fields.Dialogue Text: The Royal Lion. Guillaume's Kitten. This knocker will last a lifetime and then some.

fields.Title: Door, Basement Apartment: "Not a sound. The silence is eerie."
fields.Dialogue Text: Not a sound. The silence is eerie.

fields.Title: Suggestion: "Well buddy, you opened it. No need..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Well buddy, you opened it. No need to go inside. It would be *rude*.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Yes, presenting a fabrication is k..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yes, presenting a fabrication is known to get results here and there." He crosses his arms. "You took this task. You make the call."

fields.Title: Door, Basement Apartment: "The door is closed again. Nothing t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The door is closed again. Nothing to do here anymore.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Apparently, working with the local..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Apparently, working with the local Union boss to get info on an investigation is not something I'm squeamish about."

fields.Title: Savoir Faire: "You're *pretty* sure the owner of t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You're *pretty* sure the owner of the apartment isn't here. It's safe-ish.

fields.Title: Door, Basement Apartment: "The door is slick with rain. You do..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The door is slick with rain. You don't hear any movement inside.

fields.Title: Drama: "I don't know... you're a *pretty* g..."
fields.Dialogue Text: I don't know... you're a *pretty* good liar. Are you as good an *infiltrator* as you are a liar?

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "Besides, if you never open it, you'..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Besides, if you never open it, you're never gonna find out, what's *behind* the door.

fields.Title: Door, Basement Apartment: "This must be the door Evrart mentio..."
fields.Dialogue Text: This must be the door Evrart mentioned. You still need to get the key from Mañana first though.

fields.Title: You: "[Leave.]"
fields.Dialogue Text: [Leave.]

fields.Title: You: ""I know you're in there!""
fields.Dialogue Text: "I know you're in there!"

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""That already defeats the point, do..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "That already defeats the point, doesn't it?" The lieutenant glances at the surrounding windows. "Let's get out of here."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: "The lieutenant looks first at the d..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The lieutenant looks first at the door, then back at you, then signals you to back off from the door.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""That's probably the door Evrart me..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "That's probably the door Evrart mentioned. We still need to get the key from this Mañana first though."

fields.Title: You: ""So you don't mind if I unlock the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "So you don't mind if I unlock the door?"

fields.Title: Door, Basement Apartment: "The key stops mid-way in the lock...."
fields.Dialogue Text: The key stops mid-way in the lock. Something's blocking its path. Not a sound is coming from the apartment.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""We should leave," the lieutenant w..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "We should leave," the lieutenant whispers, "and go talk with Evrart, tell him what happened -- that we couldn't open the door. Maybe there's a workaround."

fields.Title: You: "Press your ear against the door."
fields.Dialogue Text: Press your ear against the door.

fields.Title: Door, Basement Apartment: "The leather upholstery is worn and..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The leather upholstery is worn and rough against your jaw. You don't hear any movement.

fields.Title: Endurance: "The Royal Lion. Guillaume's Kitten...."
fields.Dialogue Text: The Royal Lion. Guillaume's Kitten. This knocker will last a lifetime and then some.

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "You feel eyes on you, watching you..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You feel eyes on you, watching you from the windows overlooking the yard.

fields.Title: You: ""Lieutenant, what is your opinion o..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Lieutenant, what is your opinion of this task we're undertaking?"

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""On the other hand..." He looks at..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "On the other hand..." He looks at the surrounding windows uncomfortably. "We *could* just leave and tell Evrart we opened the door. No one seems to be tailing us to see if we actually did it."

fields.Title: Door, Basement Apartment: "You knock silently. The upholstery..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You knock silently. The upholstery muffles the sound. No response comes from the apartment.

fields.Title: You: ""Got it!""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Got it!"

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""I mind that a local thug is using..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I mind that a local thug is using the RCM for his busywork, but if this gets us to the bottom of this hanging then I'm willing to look over it."

fields.Title: Door, Basement Apartment: "You try to be as silent as you can...."
fields.Dialogue Text: You try to be as silent as you can. It takes a bit of rattling of the handle to loosen the bolt.

fields.Title: Logic: "The tenant must be cleaning up. Tha..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The tenant must be cleaning up. That means you're too late. Nothing more to do here, better report back to Evrart.

fields.Title: Door, Basement Apartment: "Something hits the ground and shatt..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Something hits the ground and shatters inside the apartment.

fields.Title: Logic: "You're too late -- the weasel's alr..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You're too late -- the weasel's already back in its den. Let's see what Evrart thinks about it.

fields.Title: Door, Basement Apartment: "As you turn to leave, you hear foot..."
fields.Dialogue Text: As you turn to leave, you hear footsteps on the other side -- yes, someone's definitely home.

fields.Title: Door, Basement Apartment: "This must be it. The basement door..."
fields.Dialogue Text: This must be it. The basement door is weather-worn. The copper nails holding the upholstery in place have turned green from sea air and there's a knocker, shaped like a lion's head.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""As I already said," the lieutenant..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "As I already said," the lieutenant replies, adjusting his glasses. "I understand this can't be avoided."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""If the merc tribunal happens befor..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "If the merc tribunal happens before we solve this..." His eyes meet yours. "We're looking at casualties. What's one unlocked door compared to that?"

fields.Title: You: ""Lie to Evrart? That's also an opti..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Lie to Evrart? That's also an option?"

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""But we do need to get the key from..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "But we do need to get the key from this 'Mañana' Evrart mentioned." The lieutenant glances at the door. "Cause we are *not* gonna break the lock."

fields.Title: You: "Knock on the door."
fields.Dialogue Text: Knock on the door.

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "Even the darkness is holding it's b..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Even the darkness is holding it's breath inside the apartment.

fields.Title: Logic: "Maybe it's a good thing you didn't..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Maybe it's a good thing you didn't get to open this stranger's door? Go talk with Evrart, tell him what happened.

fields.Title: Half Light: "You should leave. Leave! Before any..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You should leave. Leave! Before anything happens...

fields.Title: You: "[Leave.]"
fields.Dialogue Text: [Leave.]

fields.Title: Perception (Hearing): "The sound of the key turning still..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The sound of the key turning still echoes in the yard. Hopefully no one heard.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""I guess no one is in." The lieuten..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I guess no one is in." The lieutenant looks uncomfortable.

fields.Title: Door, Basement Apartment: "Then a running tap is turned off an..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Then a running tap is turned off and the complete absence of sounds feels... tense.

fields.Title: Door, Basement Apartment: "No answer."
fields.Dialogue Text: No answer.
